INSERT INTO `monuments` (`ID`, `name`, `description`, `short_description`, `mini_background`, `cover`, `video`, `address`, `directions`, `transportation`, `parking`, `accessibility`, `travelTime`, `Tips`, `contactInfo`, `map`, `country_ID`) VALUES
(1, 'Great Wall of China', 'Welcome to the awe-inspiring world of The Great Wall of China, an ancient marvel that stands as a symbol of human ingenuity and perseverance. Stretching over 13,000 miles (21,196 kilometers), it is the longest wall in the world and a testament to China\'s historical significance. Built over two millennia ago, the Great Wall has witnessed the rise and fall of empires and continues to captivate the imagination of travelers and historians alike.\n\nOriginally constructed in the 7th century BC as individual walls by different Chinese states, it was during the Qin Dynasty in the 3rd century BC that these walls were interconnected to form the iconic structure we know today. The wall\'s architectural brilliance lies in its diverse construction materials, including stone, brick, wood, and earth. Towering watchtowers were strategically placed along its length, serving as observation points and communication centers. The Great Wall\'s historical significance lies not only in its role as a formidable defensive structure against invasions but also as a symbol of national unity and the ancient Chinese civilization\'s engineering prowess.\n\nThe Great Wall of China holds immense cultural value, symbolizing the resilience and determination of the Chinese people throughout history. It has become an enduring emblem of China\'s rich heritage and global recognition as a New Seven Wonder of the World. As you explore its majestic stretches, you\'ll not only be tracing the footsteps of ancient warriors but also immersing yourself in a living testament to the indomitable spirit of the human endeavor. Visiting the Great Wall is not just a journey through history; it\'s an experience that connects you with the profound legacy of one of the world\'s most remarkable historical monuments.', 'Discover the grandeur of the Great Wall of China, an awe-inspiring architectural wonder stretching over 13,000 miles. Explore its rich history, formidable defensive structures, and breathtaking landscapes as you delve into one of the world\'s most iconic cultural landmarks.', '/IMG/Greatwall_of_China/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Greatwall_of_China/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/EotbKqZmBuY', 'The Great Wall of China stretches across multiple provinces in China, but for the most famous sections accessible from Beijing:\n\nBadaling: Badaling Great Wall, Yanqing District, Beijing, China.\nMutianyu: Mutianyu Great Wall, Huairou District, Beijing, China.\nJinshanling: Jinshanling Great Wall, Luanping County, Chengde, Hebei, China.\nSimatai: Simatai Great Wall, Gubeikou Town, Miyun District, Beijing, China.', 'The Great Wall is easily accessible from Beijing, and you can reach different sections using the following directions:\n\nBadaling: Take a bus from Deshengmen (德胜门) Bus Station to Badaling Great Wall directly. It\'s about a 1.5 to 2-hour ride.\nMutianyu: Hire a taxi, join a guided tour, or take a public bus from Dongzhimen (东直门) Transportation Hub to Mutianyu.\nJinshanling and Simatai: Consider hiring a private car or joining a guided tour, as these sections are farther from Beijing.', 'You can reach some sections of the Great Wall using public transportation:\n\nBadaling: Bus No. 877 from Deshengmen Bus Station.\nMutianyu: Take Bus No. 916 Express from Dongzhimen Transportation Hub to Huairou, then transfer to Bus No. H23 to Mutianyu Roundabout.', 'There are parking facilities available near Badaling and Mutianyu sections. Fees may apply, and parking spaces might fill up quickly during peak seasons.', ' Most sections of the Great Wall involve steep steps and uneven terrain, making it challenging for visitors with mobility issues. However, some areas, like Mutianyu, offer cable cars or chairlifts for easier access.', 'The travel time from Beijing to different sections of the Great Wall varies:\n\nBadaling: 1.5 to 2 hours.\nMutianyu: Approximately 2 hours.\nJinshanling and Simatai: Around 3 hours.', 'It\'s advisable to wear comfortable shoes and clothing suitable for hiking. Bring water and snacks, especially if you plan to explore longer sections. The Great Wall can get crowded during holidays and weekends, so consider visiting during weekdays for a quieter experience.', 'For more information or assistance, you can contact the Beijing Tourism Bureau at +86 10 6513 0828.', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d12146.366708821775!2d116.551744204998!3d40.44003959106378!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x35f121d7687f2ccf%3A0xd040259b950522df!2sGreat%20Wall%20of%20China!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690389650862!5m2!1sen!2s', 1),
(2, 'Petra', 'Step into the enchanted world of Petra, an ancient city carved into the vibrant rose-red cliffs of southern Jordan. Often referred to as the \"Rose City,\" Petra is a remarkable archaeological marvel that once served as the capital of the Nabatean Kingdom, a thriving center of trade along the ancient spice routes.\n\nDating back to around 300 BC, Petra\'s exquisite rock-cut architecture showcases a unique fusion of Hellenistic and Middle Eastern influences, making it a site of extraordinary cultural significance. As you enter through the narrow, winding Siq, a breathtaking gorge that reveals the city\'s splendor, you\'ll be greeted by the iconic Treasury (Al-Khazneh). This magnificent facade, adorned with intricate carvings, has graced the screens of many adventurers in films like \"Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade.\" Beyond the Treasury, Petra\'s labyrinthine alleyways lead you to discover the impressive Monastery (Ad-Deir), the majestic Royal Tombs, and the Great Temple.\n\nBeyond its architectural wonders, Petra is a testimony to the Nabateans\' mastery of water management. Their sophisticated irrigation system, including cisterns and channels, allowed the city to thrive in the arid desert environment.\n\nA UNESCO World Heritage Site, Petra\'s rich history and breathtaking beauty continue to captivate visitors from around the world. As you wander through its timeless ruins and immerse yourself in its enigmatic past, you\'ll find yourself transported to a lost world of ancient wonders, marveling at the legacy of a once-mighty civilization that has left an indelible mark on history.', 'Embark on a virtual journey to the ancient city of Petra, a captivating UNESCO World Heritage site nestled in the Jordanian desert. Immerse yourself in the awe-inspiring rock-cut architecture, explore intricate temples and tombs, and unravel the mysteries of this remarkable Nabataean kingdom.', '/IMG/Petra/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Petra/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/5Bdi__qG7Fc', 'Petra Archaeological Park, Petra, Ma\'an Governorate, Jordan.', 'Petra is located in southern Jordan and is accessible from various cities and airports in the country. The main point of entry is Amman, the capital city of Jordan.\n\nFrom Amman: The most common way to reach Petra is by road. You can hire a private car, take a taxi, or use a tourist bus service to travel from Amman to Petra. The journey takes around 3 to 4 hours, depending on traffic and road conditions.\n\nFrom Queen Alia International Airport: Upon arriving at the airport in Amman, you can hire a taxi or arrange for a private car transfer to Petra. Many hotels in Amman also offer shuttle services to Petra.', 'There are public buses available from Amman to Petra. The journey might take a bit longer compared to private transportation, but it\'s a budget-friendly option for travelers.\n\nJETT Buses: The Jordan Express Tourist Transportation Company (JETT) operates daily buses from the JETT bus station in Amman to Petra. The journey takes approximately 3.5 to 4 hours.', 'If you\'re driving to Petra in a private car, there are parking facilities available near the entrance to the archaeological park. Parking fees may apply.', 'The main entrance to Petra, known as the Siq, involves walking through a narrow and rocky canyon. Visitors with mobility challenges can hire a horse-drawn carriage or a horseback ride for part of the way. However, some areas inside Petra, such as the Monastery and High Place of Sacrifice, require hiking uphill, which might not be suitable for everyone.', 'The travel time from Amman to Petra is approximately 3 to 4 hours by road.', 'Wear comfortable shoes suitable for walking and exploring rocky terrain. Bring plenty of water, especially if you plan to hike to the Monastery or other distant sites within Petra. Sunscreen and a hat are essential, as the sun can be intense in the desert. It\'s also advisable to carry cash in Jordanian Dinar (JOD), as not all places accept credit cards.', 'For more information or assistance, you can contact the Petra Development and Tourism Region Authority at +962 3 215 7090.', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3443.79127274369!2d35.4417819110484!3d30.32845437467662!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x15016ef1703b6071%3A0x199bf908679a2291!2sPetra!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690389933398!5m2!1sen!2s', 2),
(3, 'Christ the Redeemer Statue', 'Prepare to be awe-struck by the magnificent Christ the Redeemer Statue, an iconic symbol of faith and unity that graces the cityscape of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. Perched atop the peak of Corcovado Mountain, this colossal Art Deco statue stands at an impressive height of 98 feet (30 meters) with its outstretched arms spanning 92 feet (28 meters), welcoming visitors from all corners of the globe.\n\nDesigned by French sculptor Paul Landowski and completed in 1931, Christ the Redeemer overlooks the city, offering a panoramic view that takes in the sparkling blue waters of Guanabara Bay and the bustling urban landscape below. As a testament to Brazil\'s deep-rooted devotion, the statue symbolizes not only a religious icon but also a beacon of hope and love, transcending cultural and religious boundaries.\n\nEmbodying the message of peace and compassion, Christ the Redeemer is an enduring tribute to the Brazilian people\'s warm and welcoming spirit. Its construction required meticulous planning and engineering, a true testament to human determination and creativity.\n\nToday, this UNESCO World Heritage Site stands as an architectural masterpiece, captivating millions of visitors who come to experience its spiritual aura and witness the harmonious blend of nature and man-made wonder. As you stand before the Christ the Redeemer Statue, you\'ll be moved by its powerful presence, touched by the universal message of love, and inspired to embrace unity and understanding among all humanity.', 'Experience the magnificence of the Christ the Redeemer Statue, an iconic symbol overlooking the vibrant city of Rio de Janeiro. Discover the statue\'s rich history, breathtaking views, and its role as a universal symbol of peace, unity, and faith in the heart of Brazil.', '/IMG/Christ_the_Redeemer_statue/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Christ_the_Redeemer_statue/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/oq-2m2diCy8', 'Corcovado, Rio de Janeiro - RJ, 22241-330, Brazil.', 'The most iconic and popular way to reach Christ the Redeemer is by taking the Corcovado Train. The train departs from the base of the Corcovado Mountain, and the journey offers scenic views of the Tijuca Forest and the city of Rio de Janeiro. The train takes approximately 20 minutes to reach the top.\n\nBy Van or Taxi: Visitors can also take vans or taxis to the Christ the Redeemer entrance at the Corcovado Mountain. Vans are available from various points in the city, including the Largo do Machado square. The ride to the top takes around 30 minutes, depending on traffic.\n\nBy Hiking: For the more adventurous travelers, there are hiking trails that lead to the Christ the Redeemer Statue. The most common trail starts from Parque Lage and takes about 2 to 3 hours to reach the summit.', 'There are no direct public transportation options to the Christ the Redeemer entrance. Visitors usually take a combination of buses and vans or taxis to reach the starting point for the train or vans.', 'If you prefer to drive to the Corcovado Mountain, there is a parking lot available at the base of the mountain where you can leave your vehicle while visiting the statue.', 'The Corcovado Train and vans are accessible to most visitors. However, it\'s important to note that the final stretch to the statue\'s platform involves a series of steep ramps and stairs, which might be challenging for individuals with mobility impairments.', 'The travel time to reach Christ the Redeemer depends on the mode of transportation chosen. The train ride takes about 20 minutes, while the van or taxi ride from Largo do Machado takes approximately 30 minutes. Hiking can take 2 to 3 hours, depending on the starting point and hiking speed.', 'It\'s recommended to visit Christ the Redeemer early in the morning or later in the afternoon to avoid crowds. Be prepared for changing weather conditions, as the statue is often shrouded in clouds. Bring your camera to capture the breathtaking views of Rio de Janeiro from the top.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can contact the local tourist website of Christ the Redeemer: <a href=\'https://en.santuariocristoredentor.com.br\' target=\'_blank\'>en.santuariocristoredentor.com.br</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d14695.812610150057!2d-43.221485106534004!3d-22.951952366183477!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x997fd5984aa13f%3A0x9dc984d7019502de!2sChrist%20the%20Redeemer!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690390089672!5m2!1sen!2s', 5),
(4, 'Machu Picchu', 'Embark on a mystical journey to the ancient Inca citadel of Machu Picchu, perched high in the Andes Mountains of Peru. Often referred to as the \"Lost City of the Incas,\" Machu Picchu is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the most captivating archaeological wonders on Earth.\n\nBuilt in the 15th century by the Inca Emperor Pachacuti, Machu Picchu served as a sacred retreat and a center of spiritual significance. This enigmatic city was abandoned a mere century after its construction and remained hidden from the outside world for centuries until its rediscovery in 1911 by Hiram Bingham.\n\nAs you navigate the terraced fields, intricate stonework, and majestic temples, you\'ll be immersed in the Inca civilization\'s profound connection with nature and the celestial world. The Temple of the Sun, the Intihuatana stone, and the Room of the Three Windows are just a few of the remarkable structures that reveal the Inca\'s advanced understanding of astronomy and architecture.\n\nMachu Picchu\'s awe-inspiring setting amidst the lush Andean landscape, surrounded by mist-shrouded peaks, evokes a sense of wonder and tranquility. The site\'s spiritual energy and the mysteries shrouding its purpose continue to spark intrigue and fascination among historians, archaeologists, and visitors alike. As you explore this ancient sanctuary, you\'ll be transported to a time long past, gaining a deeper appreciation for the ingenuity and spiritual beliefs of the Inca civilization that once thrived in the heart of the Andes.', 'Embark on a virtual exploration of Machu Picchu, the legendary ancient city nestled in the Andes Mountains. Uncover the secrets of the Inca civilization, marvel at the breathtaking mountain vistas, and immerse yourself in the mystical allure of this UNESCO World Heritage site.', '/IMG/Machu_Picchu/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Machu_Picchu/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/oZ90M55mDac', 'Machu Picchu, Urubamba Province, Peru.', 'Machu Picchu is located in the Andes Mountains of Peru and is one of the most iconic archaeological sites in the world. To reach Machu Picchu, follow these steps:\n\n1. Fly to Cusco: The journey to Machu Picchu typically starts with a flight to Cusco, the nearest major city. Alejandro Velasco Astete International Airport in Cusco is well-connected with several international and domestic flights.\n\n2. Travel to Aguas Calientes: From Cusco, take a train or bus to Aguas Calientes, the gateway town to Machu Picchu. The train journey offers stunning views of the Andean landscapes and takes around 3 to 4 hours, depending on the service chosen. Alternatively, you can take a bus from Cusco to the town, which takes approximately 6 to 7 hours.\n\n3. Machu Picchu Entrance: From Aguas Calientes, visitors can access Machu Picchu by either hiking up the Inca Trail or taking a shuttle bus to the entrance. The bus ride takes about 30 minutes, while the classic Inca Trail trek requires a multi-day hike and must be booked well in advance. There are also alternative shorter hiking routes available, such as the Huayna Picchu or Machu Picchu Mountain hikes.', 'The most common way to reach Machu Picchu is by train or bus from Cusco to Aguas Calientes. Once in Aguas Calientes, visitors can take a shuttle bus or hike to the Machu Picchu entrance.', 'Private vehicles are not allowed at Machu Picchu. If you are traveling by car or tour bus, you will need to park in Aguas Calientes and continue to Machu Picchu on foot or by shuttle bus.', 'While the shuttle bus to the Machu Picchu entrance is accessible, the site itself has uneven terrain and steep stairs, which might be challenging for visitors with mobility limitations.', 'The total travel time to reach Machu Picchu from Cusco varies depending on the mode of transportation chosen. The train journey from Cusco to Aguas Calientes takes around 3 to 4 hours, while the bus journey takes approximately 6 to 7 hours. The shuttle bus from Aguas Calientes to the Machu Picchu entrance takes about 30 minutes.', 'Due to the high demand and limited daily entry tickets, it\'s advisable to book your Machu Picchu tickets and train/bus tickets well in advance. Carry essential items such as water, sunscreen, a hat, and comfortable walking shoes for your visit. Respect the rules and regulations at the site, including not touching or climbing on the ancient structures.', ' For more information or inquiries, you can visit the official website of the Peruvian Ministry of Culture: <a href=\'https://www.machupicchu.gob.pe\' target=\'_blank\'>www.machupicchu.gob.pe</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3883.983838562914!2d-72.49990178944805!3d-13.22633078705917!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x916d9a5f89555555%3A0x3a10370ea4a01a27!2sMachu%20Picchu!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690390460015!5m2!1sen!2s', 6),
(5, 'Chichen Itza', 'Journey back in time to the ancient city of Chichen Itza, located in the lush Yucatán Peninsula of Mexico. This captivating UNESCO World Heritage Site stands as a testament to the extraordinary achievements of the Maya civilization, a true gem of Mesoamerican culture.\n\nDating back to the late pre-classical period, around 600 AD, Chichen Itza rose to prominence as a major center of trade, religion, and politics. Its strategic location allowed it to thrive as a hub for the exchange of goods and ideas among neighboring cities.\n\nAs you enter this archaeological wonder, you\'ll be greeted by the awe-inspiring pyramid known as El Castillo, or the Temple of Kukulkan. This iconic structure demonstrates the Maya\'s advanced astronomical knowledge, with 91 steps on each of its four sides, totaling 365 steps, representing the solar calendar.\n\nChichen Itza\'s architectural brilliance extends beyond El Castillo, with other notable structures like the Great Ball Court, where ancient sporting events took place, and the Temple of the Warriors, adorned with intricate carvings and statues. Additionally, the sacred cenote, a natural sinkhole once used for religious ceremonies and offerings, offers a glimpse into the spiritual beliefs of the Maya people.\n\nAs you traverse through this historical marvel, you\'ll gain insight into the sophisticated urban planning, artistry, and mathematical precision that characterized the Maya civilization. Chichen Itza\'s timeless allure and its blend of architectural grandeur and cultural significance continue to captivate the minds of visitors, inviting you to uncover the rich tapestry of an ancient civilization that flourished in the heart of the Yucatán Peninsula.', 'Embark on a virtual expedition to Chichen Itza, an awe-inspiring archaeological site in Mexico. Uncover the mysteries of the ancient Maya civilization as you explore the iconic El Castillo pyramid, the sacred cenote, and the intricate Temple of the Warriors. Immerse yourself in the rich history, vibrant culture, and architectural wonders of this UNESCO World Heritage site, and discover why Chichen Itza continues to captivate visitors with its timeless beauty and profound cultural significance.', '/IMG/Chichen_Itza/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Chichen_Itza/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/SxM22NB-qW8', 'Chichen Itza, Yucatan, Mexico.', 'Chichen Itza is a famous archaeological site located in the Yucatan Peninsula of Mexico. To reach Chichen Itza, follow these steps:\r\n\r\n1. Fly to Cancun: The journey to Chichen Itza typically starts with a flight to Cancun International Airport, which is well-connected with various international and domestic flights.\r\n\r\n2. Travel to Chichen Itza: From Cancun, Chichen Itza is approximately a 2 to 2.5-hour drive. Visitors have several transportation options to reach the site:\r\n\r\n+ Rental Car: Renting a car allows for flexibility and independence in exploring the region. The drive from Cancun to Chichen Itza is straightforward and well-marked.\r\n\r\n- Organized Tour: Joining an organized tour is a convenient option, as it includes transportation, a knowledgeable guide, and entrance fees to the site.\r\n\r\n- Public Transportation: Public buses operate from Cancun to Piste, the town closest to Chichen Itza. From Piste, visitors can take a short taxi ride to the archaeological site.', 'Public buses operate between Cancun and Piste, the nearest town to Chichen Itza. From Piste, visitors can take a taxi to reach the archaeological site.', 'If you are driving to Chichen Itza, there are parking facilities available near the site for a fee.', 'Chichen Itza is relatively accessible to visitors with paved pathways and ramps at certain areas. However, some parts of the site may have uneven terrain and stairs.', 'The travel time from Cancun to Chichen Itza is approximately 2 to 2.5 hours by car or bus.', 'Chichen Itza is a popular tourist destination, so it\'s recommended to arrive early in the day to avoid crowds and the heat. Wear comfortable clothing, a hat, and sturdy footwear, as you\'ll be doing a fair amount of walking during your visit. Bring sunscreen and stay hydrated. Remember to respect the archaeological site by not climbing on the ruins or touching the ancient structures.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can visit the official website of Chichen Itza: <a href=\'https://www.chichenitza.com\' target=\'_blank\'>www.chichenitza.com</a>\r\n', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3732.7198927240224!2d-88.57105718927745!3d20.680971830803042!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x8f5138c6e391c0e7%3A0x7c1ea0a168994d9a!2zQ2hpY2jDqW4gSXR6w6E!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690390626548!5m2!1sen!2s', 7),
(6, 'Colosseum', 'Step into the majestic world of the Colosseum, an ancient amphitheater that stands as an enduring symbol of Rome\'s grandeur and cultural legacy. Located in the heart of the Italian capital, the Colosseum, also known as the Flavian Amphitheatre, is an architectural marvel that has withstood the test of time.\n\nCompleted in AD 80 during the reign of Emperor Titus, the Colosseum was built to host gladiatorial contests, animal hunts, and elaborate public spectacles. Its construction was an ambitious endeavor, utilizing sophisticated engineering techniques and innovative solutions that allowed for quick assembly and disassembly of the stage sets.\n\nAs you stand within the immense walls of this elliptical amphitheater, you\'ll be transported to a time of ancient Roman entertainment and the gladiatorial games that captivated the masses. The Colosseum\'s tiered seating could accommodate up to 50,000 spectators, providing an unrivaled venue for communal gatherings and showcasing the power and splendor of the Roman Empire.\n\nThe arena\'s floor, once covered with sand, witnessed fierce battles between gladiators and wild animals, as well as naval reenactments. Today, the Colosseum\'s ruins evoke a sense of wonder, as visitors explore the labyrinth of passages and archways that have witnessed centuries of history.\n\nA UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Colosseum remains a symbol of Roman engineering prowess and a testament to the rich cultural heritage that has shaped the world. As you delve into the history of this iconic monument, you\'ll gain a deeper appreciation for the ancient civilization that once thrived amidst its imposing walls and the enduring legacy of one of the greatest civilizations in human history.', ' Step into history with a virtual visit to the Colosseum, the awe-inspiring amphitheater that once hosted spectacular events in ancient Rome. Dive into its architectural splendor, learn about thrilling gladiatorial contests, and immerse yourself in the rich legacy of the Roman Empire.', '/IMG/Colosseum/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Colosseum/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/fTVXfRooqLg', 'Colosseum, Piazza del Colosseo, 1, 00184 Roma RM, Italy', 'Directions from Rome City Center:\r\n\r\nBy Metro: Take Line B (Blue Line) towards Laurentina and get off at the Colosseo station. The Colosseum is just a short walk from the station.\r\nBy Bus: Multiple bus lines, including 75, 81, 85, 87, and 117, stop near the Colosseum. Get off at the \"Colosseo\" or \"Fori Imperiali\" stop.\r\nDirections from Leonardo da Vinci International Airport (Fiumicino Airport):\r\n\r\nBy Train: Take the Leonardo Express train from the airport to Roma Termini (main railway station). From Roma Termini, take Metro Line B to the Colosseo station.\r\nBy Taxi: Taxis are available at the airport. It\'s approximately a 30-40 minute drive to the Colosseum, depending on traffic.', 'The Colosseum is well-connected by public transportation. The Metro and various bus lines provide easy access to the monument.', 'Limited parking spaces are available near the Colosseum. However, it\'s recommended to use public transportation as parking can be challenging, especially during peak hours.', 'The Colosseum offers accessibility options for visitors with disabilities. Wheelchair-accessible ramps and elevators are available for those in need.', 'From Rome City Center: It takes around 15-20 minutes to reach the Colosseum from the central area of Rome by public transportation.\nFrom Fiumicino Airport: The travel time from the airport to the Colosseum is approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on the mode of transportation and traffic conditions.', 'The Colosseum is a popular tourist attraction, so it\'s advisable to arrive early to avoid long ticket lines.\nWear comfortable shoes, as you\'ll be doing a fair amount of walking at the monument and in the surrounding archaeological area.', 'Colosseum Information Desk: +39 06 3996 7700\nColosseum Ticket Office: +39 06 3996 7700', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2970.1230728428554!2d12.4922309!3d41.890210200000006!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x132f61b6532013ad%3A0x28f1c82e908503c4!2sColosseum!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690384596196!5m2!1sen!2s', 8),
(7, 'Taj Mahal', 'Welcome to the ethereal beauty of the Taj Mahal, an iconic symbol of love and architectural masterpiece located in Agra, India. Commissioned by Emperor Shah Jahan in the 17th century, this awe-inspiring marble mausoleum stands as a poignant tribute to his beloved wife, Mumtaz Mahal, who passed away during childbirth.\n\nNestled on the banks of the Yamuna River, the Taj Mahal reflects the perfect harmony of Persian, Islamic, and Indian architectural styles, showcasing the zenith of Mughal architecture. Its glistening white marble facade is adorned with intricate inlays of semi-precious stones, evoking a sense of delicate craftsmanship and artistic finesse.\n\nAs you approach the Taj Mahal, the grand entrance gate frames the mausoleum like a picturesque picture frame, adding to the mystique of the monument. The symmetrical gardens and reflecting pools create a mesmerizing sense of balance and serenity, accentuating the majestic presence of the central marble structure.\n\nInside the Taj Mahal\'s central chamber lies the elegantly crafted sarcophagi of Emperor Shah Jahan and Mumtaz Mahal, a testament to the depth of love that inspired this breathtaking creation.\n\nDesignated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Taj Mahal stands as a timeless symbol of eternal love and an enduring tribute to the rich cultural heritage of India. As you stand before this architectural wonder, you\'ll be captivated by its beauty, its romantic tale, and its profound impact on the world\'s artistic and architectural legacy. The Taj Mahal\'s ethereal charm leaves an indelible mark on the hearts of all who witness its magnificence, reaffirming its status as one of the most beloved and iconic monuments in the world.', 'Indulge in the timeless beauty of the Taj Mahal, a mesmerizing monument of love in Agra, India. Explore the exquisite architecture, delve into the poignant love story behind its creation, and bask in the ethereal charm of this UNESCO World Heritage site.', '/IMG/Taj_Mahal/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Taj_Mahal/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/RDiq-kJ2xTg', 'Dharmapuri, Forest Colony, Tajganj, Agra, Uttar Pradesh 282001, India.', 'The Taj Mahal is located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. To reach the Taj Mahal, follow these steps:\n\n1. Fly to Delhi: The journey to the Taj Mahal usually starts with a flight to Indira Gandhi International Airport in Delhi, which is well-connected to major cities worldwide.\n\n2. Travel to Agra: From Delhi, Agra is approximately a 3 to 4-hour drive, depending on traffic conditions. Visitors have several transportation options to reach Agra:\n\n- Train: Agra is well-connected by train from Delhi and other major cities in India. You can take a train from New Delhi Railway Station to Agra Cantt Railway Station.\n\n- Private Car or Taxi: Hiring a private car or taxi from Delhi to Agra is a convenient option, especially for groups or families.\n\n- Bus: There are also comfortable air-conditioned buses that run between Delhi and Agra, operated by various private and government agencies.\n\n3. Arriving in Agra: Once in Agra, follow the signs directing you to the Taj Mahal. The monument is easily accessible by road, and there are clear directions on major roads leading to the site.', 'Agra is well-connected by train and bus services from major cities in India. From Agra, visitors can take a local bus, auto-rickshaw, or taxi to reach the Taj Mahal.', 'If you are driving to the Taj Mahal, there are parking facilities available near the monument. However, private vehicles are not allowed in the immediate vicinity of the Taj Mahal complex, so you will need to take a battery-operated bus or walk to the entrance.', 'The Taj Mahal complex is equipped with ramps and accessible pathways for visitors with disabilities.', 'The travel time from Delhi to Agra is approximately 3 to 4 hours by car, 2 to 3 hours by train, and 4 to 5 hours by bus.', 'The Taj Mahal is one of the most popular tourist attractions in the world, so it\'s advisable to arrive early in the morning to avoid long queues and crowds. The monument is closed on Fridays. Dress modestly and respect the cultural significance of the site. Avoid carrying large bags or prohibited items inside the complex. Photography is allowed but not permitted inside the main mausoleum.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can visit the official website of the Archaeological Survey of India: <a href=\'https://www.tajmahal.gov.in\' target=\'_blank\'>tajmahal.gov.in</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3549.4005540607654!2d78.03956191092925!3d27.1751447763936!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39747121d702ff6d%3A0xdd2ae4803f767dde!2sTaj%20Mahal!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690460190567!5m2!1sen!2s', 3),
(8, 'Statue of Liberty', 'Behold the majestic Lady Liberty, an iconic symbol of freedom and democracy, proudly standing on Liberty Island in New York Harbor, USA. Gifted to the United States by France in 1886, the Statue of Liberty has become an enduring emblem of hope and opportunity, welcoming millions of immigrants arriving on American shores.\n\nDesigned by French sculptor Frédéric Auguste Bartholdi, with its framework engineered by Alexandre Gustave Eiffel, the statue rises to a height of 305 feet (93 meters) from the ground to the tip of the torch. Her radiant crown, seven rays representing the seven continents, symbolizes universal enlightenment and liberty.\n\nThe Statue of Liberty\'s torch, held high, illuminates the path to freedom and beckons those seeking a better life and a refuge from oppression. As a powerful visual symbol, she reminds the world of the United States\' commitment to liberty, justice, and human rights.\n\nAccessible via a ferry ride from Battery Park, the Statue of Liberty offers breathtaking views of the Manhattan skyline and the harbor. The pedestal museum delves into the statue\'s history, construction, and its significance as an enduring beacon of democracy.\n\nAs you stand before Lady Liberty, you\'ll be moved by the powerful embodiment of American values and the universal ideals she represents. The Statue of Liberty remains a cherished symbol of freedom for people around the globe, inspiring hope and resilience, and reminding us of the enduring power of liberty and the pursuit of a brighter future.', 'Experience the essence of freedom with a virtual encounter with the Statue of Liberty, an enduring symbol of hope and democracy in New York Harbor. Discover the history, significance, and architectural magnificence of Lady Liberty, and be inspired by the ideals she represents.', '/IMG/Statue_of_Liberty/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Statue_of_Liberty/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/Q9WcBGJh8ng', 'Liberty Island, New York, NY 10004, United States.', 'The Statue of Liberty is located on Liberty Island in New York Harbor. To reach the Statue of Liberty, follow these steps:\n\n1. Fly to New York City: The journey to the Statue of Liberty usually starts with a flight to one of the airports in New York City, such as John F. Kennedy International Airport (JFK) or LaGuardia Airport (LGA).\n\n2. Travel to Battery Park, Manhattan: From the airport, you can take a taxi, shuttle service, or public transportation to Battery Park in Lower Manhattan, which is the departure point for the Statue of Liberty ferry.\n\n3. Statue of Liberty Ferry: To visit the Statue of Liberty, you must take a ferry from Battery Park to Liberty Island. The Statue of Liberty and Ellis Island are part of the same national monument, and the ferry ticket usually includes both attractions. Tickets can be purchased online or at the ticket counters in Battery Park.\n\n4. Visiting the Statue of Liberty: Once you arrive on Liberty Island, you can explore the grounds and visit the Statue of Liberty\'s pedestal or crown if you have reserved tickets in advance.', 'New York City has an extensive public transportation system. You can take the subway or bus to Battery Park or use ride-sharing services to reach the departure point for the ferry.', 'If you prefer to drive to Battery Park, there are parking facilities available in the area, but parking in Manhattan can be expensive. Consider using public transportation or ride-sharing options to avoid parking hassles.', 'The Statue of Liberty and Liberty Island are accessible to visitors with disabilities. There are elevators to the pedestal level, but access to the crown involves climbing stairs.', 'The travel time from New York City airports to Battery Park varies depending on traffic conditions but typically takes around 30 minutes to an hour.', 'The Statue of Liberty is a popular attraction, and tickets for the crown and pedestal often sell out quickly, so it\'s advisable to book tickets in advance. Security checks are conducted before boarding the ferry, so arrive early to allow time for the screening process. Be prepared for long lines during peak tourist seasons.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can visit the official National Park Service website: <a href=\'https://www.statueoflibertytickets.com\' target=\'_blank\'>statueoflibertytickets.com</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3025.3063877890836!2d-74.0470806884798!3d40.689249371277675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89c25090129c363d%3A0x40c6a5770d25022b!2sStatue%20of%20Liberty!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690460432929!5m2!1sen!2s', 10),
(9, 'Arc de Triomphe', 'Welcome to the grandeur of the Arc de Triomphe, an iconic symbol of French national pride located in the heart of Paris, France. Commissioned by Napoleon Bonaparte in 1806 to honor the French army\'s victories, this monumental triumphal arch stands at the western end of the prestigious Champs-Élysées avenue.\n\nDesigned by architect Jean-François-Thérèse Chalgrin, the Arc de Triomphe showcases an impressive Neoclassical design, adorned with intricate sculptures and bas-reliefs depicting historic battles and patriotic scenes. The names of over 600 generals and the victories of the French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars are inscribed on its walls, attesting to its significance as a national memorial.\n\nThe Arc de Triomphe serves as a focal point for various grand military parades and public celebrations, symbolizing the French people\'s resilience and unity in times of triumph and adversity.\n\nVisitors can ascend the arch to the viewing platform at the top, offering breathtaking panoramic views of the city, with avenues radiating out like spokes of a wheel. From this vantage point, the splendor of Paris stretches out before you, showcasing its timeless beauty and architectural heritage.\n\nThe Arc de Triomphe stands as an enduring reminder of France\'s rich history, valor, and cultural legacy. It serves as a powerful testament to the country\'s commitment to liberty, equality, and fraternity, resonating with locals and visitors alike as a symbol of national identity and unity. As you explore this historic monument, you\'ll feel immersed in the spirit of France and gain a profound appreciation for the enduring values that have shaped the nation\'s history and character.', 'Uncover the grandeur of the Arc de Triomphe, an iconic monument standing proudly at the heart of Paris. Admire its neoclassical design, learn about its historical significance, and immerse yourself in the spirit of triumph and unity that defines this remarkable French landmark.', '/IMG/Arc_de_Triomphe/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Arc_de_Triomphe/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/JgWhagB4d_g', 'Place Charles de Gaulle, 75008 Paris, France.', 'The Arc de Triomphe is situated in the heart of Paris at the western end of the Champs-Élysées. Here\'s how to get to the Arc de Triomphe:\n\nFly to Paris: If you are arriving from abroad, you can fly to one of Paris\'s international airports, such as Charles de Gaulle Airport (CDG) or Orly Airport (ORY).\n\n- Public Transportation: From the airport or any other location in Paris, you can use the city\'s efficient public transportation system. Take the metro or bus to Charles de Gaulle - Étoile station, which is directly connected to the Arc de Triomphe.\n\n- Walking: The Arc de Triomphe is accessible by foot from various points in central Paris, especially if you are staying in the vicinity of the Champs-Élysées.', 'Metro: Take Line 1, Line 2, or Line 6 to Charles de Gaulle - Étoile station.\nRER: Take Line A to Charles de Gaulle - Étoile station.', ' If you plan to drive, be aware that the traffic around the Arc de Triomphe can be busy, as it is a major traffic circle. Paid parking is available nearby.', 'The Arc de Triomphe is partially accessible to visitors with reduced mobility. There is an elevator to the terrace level, but access to the museum inside the monument involves climbing stairs.', ' The travel time to the Arc de Triomphe from the main airports or major train stations in Paris typically ranges from 30 minutes to an hour, depending on the mode of transportation and traffic conditions.', 'When visiting the Arc de Triomphe, use the underground pedestrian passage at the Avenue de la Grande Armée to access the monument safely, as the traffic around the circle is quite busy. Also, consider arriving early in the morning or during weekdays to avoid large crowds.', 'For further information or inquiries, you can visit the official website: <a href=\'https://www.paris-arc-de-triomphe.fr/en\' target=\'_blank\'>www.paris-arc-de-triomphe.fr/en</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.182803620141!2d2.290161953032306!3d48.87379159764762!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66fec70fb1d8f%3A0xd9b5676e112e643d!2sArc%20de%20Triomphe!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690460995140!5m2!1sen!2s', 9),
(10, 'Halong Bay', 'Embark on a mesmerizing voyage through the captivating landscapes of Halong Bay, Vietnam\'s crown jewel and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Located in the Gulf of Tonkin in northeastern Vietnam, Halong Bay is a natural wonder characterized by its emerald waters, towering limestone karsts, and lush greenery.\n\nLegend has it that the bay was formed by a descending dragon, giving it its name, \"Halong,\" which means \"descending dragon.\" As you cruise through the serene waters, you\'ll be surrounded by thousands of limestone islets and towering pillars, each seemingly sculpted by nature\'s hand.\n\nThe bay\'s ethereal beauty is complemented by numerous hidden caves and grottoes that hold historical and cultural significance, with stalactites and stalagmites forming stunning natural sculptures. Thien Cung Cave and Sung Sot Cave are just a few of the magnificent wonders awaiting your exploration.\n\nHalong Bay\'s floating fishing villages add a touch of authenticity to the experience, allowing you to witness the unique way of life of the local fishing communities.\n\nAs you venture into the heart of Halong Bay, you\'ll be enchanted by the tranquility and breathtaking vistas that surround you, making it a photographer\'s paradise and a haven for nature lovers. This mystical bay, with its blend of natural beauty and cultural charm, promises an unforgettable adventure, leaving you with memories of a landscape that feels almost otherworldly. Halong Bay\'s timeless allure continues to captivate travelers, beckoning them to uncover the secrets of a place where the heavens seem to meet the earth in a breathtaking symphony of beauty and harmony.', 'Embark on a virtual voyage to the enchanting Halong Bay, a natural wonder nestled in the Gulf of Tonkin, Vietnam. Witness the mesmerizing beauty of limestone karsts, explore hidden caves, and immerse yourself in the tranquility of this UNESCO World Heritage site.', '/IMG/Halong_Bay/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Halong_Bay/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/fAS29vl-RPY', 'Halong Bay, Quang Ninh Province, Vietnam.', 'Halong Bay is located in northeastern Vietnam and is accessible from various major cities in the country. Here\'s how to get to Halong Bay:\n\n1. Fly to Hanoi: The nearest major international airport to Halong Bay is Noi Bai International Airport (HAN) in Hanoi. If you are arriving from abroad, fly to Hanoi first.\n\n2. Pick your prefered transportation method to Halong Bay:\n- Shuttle Bus or Private Transfer: From Hanoi, you can take a shuttle bus or arrange for a private transfer to Halong Bay. The journey takes approximately 3 to 4 hours, depending on traffic conditions.\n\n- Cruise Tours: Many visitors choose to explore Halong Bay through cruise tours. These tours typically depart from the Tuan Chau International Marina or Hon Gai Port, both of which are easily accessible from Hanoi.\n\n- Seaplane: For a unique and scenic experience, consider taking a seaplane from Hanoi to Halong Bay. Some tour operators offer seaplane transfers that provide stunning aerial views of the bay.\n\n3. Arriving in Halong Bay: Once you arrive in Halong Bay, head to your designated cruise or accommodation. Most cruises depart from Tuan Chau International Marina or Hon Gai Port.', 'There are several companies operate shuttle buses as well as tour buses between Hanoi and Halong Bay. These buses have very comfortable seating and are equipped with air conditioning.', 'If you\'re traveling to Halong Bay by private vehicle or taking a shuttle bus from Hanoi, there are parking facilities available near the Tuan Chau International Marina and Hon Gai Port. These parking areas are well-maintained and provide a secure place to park your vehicle during your visit to Halong Bay.', 'Halong Bay cruises and tours may vary in terms of accessibility for visitors with disabilities. It\'s recommended to inquire with your chosen tour operator or cruise company about their accessibility options and facilities.', 'The travel time from Hanoi to Halong Bay is approximately 3 to 4 hours by road, depending on traffic conditions.', '- Halong Bay is a popular tourist destination, so it\'s advisable to plan your trip and book accommodations in advance, especially during peak seasons.\n- Respect the environment and follow responsible tourism practices to preserve the natural beauty of the bay.\n- Be cautious of your belongings and keep an eye on your valuables, especially in crowded areas.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can contact the following Halong Bay local travel guide here at: <a href=\'https://www.visithalongbay.com\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.visithalongbay.com</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d238440.43164375285!2d106.87771862183239!3d20.96729881380177!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x314a583f825ff2c9%3A0xc5d143510be28d44!2zSOG6oSBMb25nLCBRdeG6o25nIE5pbmgsIFZpZXRuYW0!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690463017105!5m2!1sen!2s', 4);
INSERT INTO `monuments` (`ID`, `name`, `description`, `short_description`, `mini_background`, `cover`, `video`, `address`, `directions`, `transportation`, `parking`, `accessibility`, `travelTime`, `Tips`, `contactInfo`, `map`, `country_ID`) VALUES
(11, 'Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum', 'In the heart of Hanoi, Vietnam, lies the solemn and revered Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum, a place of deep reverence and historical significance. This monumental structure serves as the final resting place of the beloved leader of Vietnam, Ho Chi Minh, who played a crucial role in the country\'s struggle for independence and unification.\n\nHo Chi Minh, affectionately known as \"Uncle Ho,\" was the founding father of modern Vietnam and the first President of the Democratic Republic of Vietnam. His unwavering dedication to the welfare of his people and his vision of a united and independent nation earned him immense respect and admiration among Vietnamese citizens.\n\nThe mausoleum\'s architectural design exudes simplicity and dignity, reflecting Ho Chi Minh\'s modest and humble nature. His preserved body lies in state within a glass sarcophagus, allowing visitors to pay their respects and honor the memory of this extraordinary leader.\n\nThe mausoleum\'s location in Ba Dinh Square, surrounded by important landmarks such as the Presidential Palace and the Ho Chi Minh Museum, underscores its significance as the focal point of the nation\'s political and historical heritage.\n\nVisiting the Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum offers a profound opportunity to connect with the history and the enduring legacy of Ho Chi Minh, a man whose ideals and principles continue to shape Vietnam\'s identity and aspirations. As you stand before the mausoleum, you\'ll feel a sense of solemnity and gratitude for the remarkable life and contributions of a leader who devoted himself to the liberation and prosperity of his beloved homeland.', 'Pay tribute to a visionary leader with a virtual visit to the Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum in Hanoi, Vietnam. Discover the solemnity of this revered site, honor the legacy of Ho Chi Minh, and reflect upon the nation\'s struggle for independence and social justice.', '/IMG/HCM_Mausoleum/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/HCM_Mausoleum/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/SG1vJj9WHKI', '2 Hung Vuong, Dien Bien, Ba Dinh, Hanoi, Vietnam.', 'To get to Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum follow these steps:\n\n1. Fly to Hanoi: The journey to Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum usually starts with a flight to Noi Bai International Airport in Hanoi, Vietnam. The airport is well-connected to major cities and countries around the world.\n\n2. Travel to Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum: From Hanoi, you can travel to Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum by road, which takes approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on traffic conditions. There are several transportation options available:\n\n- Taxi or Ride-Sharing: Taking a taxi or using ride-sharing services is a convenient and direct way to reach the mausoleum. It\'s recommended to use reputable taxi companies.\n\n- Public Bus: You can also take a public bus to reach the mausoleum. Buses in Hanoi are well-connected, and there are designated bus stops near the mausoleum.\n\n3. Arriving at Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum: Once you arrive at the mausoleum, you will find designated visitor entrances. The mausoleum is a prominent landmark, making it easy to locate.', 'Hanoi has an extensive public bus network. Look for buses that pass through Ba Dinh Square or the nearby areas to reach the mausoleum.', ' If you\'re traveling to Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum by private vehicle, there are parking facilities available nearby. However, it\'s important to note that visitors are not allowed to park their vehicles directly at the mausoleum grounds.', 'Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum is designed to be accessible to all visitors. There are ramps and facilities for visitors with disabilities to ensure a smooth and respectful visit.', 'The travel time from Hanoi city center to Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum is approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on the mode of transportation and traffic conditions.', '- Dress appropriately and respectfully when visiting the mausoleum. Avoid wearing sleeveless shirts, shorts, or revealing clothing.\n- Photography inside the mausoleum is strictly prohibited, so please follow the rules and guidelines set by the authorities.\n- The mausoleum has specific visiting hours, so check the schedule in advance to plan your visit accordingly.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can contact the Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum Management Board here: <a href=\'https://www.bqllang.gov.vn\' target=\'_blank\'>https://www.bqllang.gov.vn</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3723.927265931894!2d105.83002681073238!3d21.03559608053454!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3135aba02e1deb6f%3A0x949d893f040b49d1!2sHo%20Chi%20Minh%20Museum!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1691179559838!5m2!1sen!2s', 4),
(12, 'Great Pyramid of Giza', 'Welcome to the realm of ancient wonder, where the Great Pyramid of Giza stands as a timeless testament to human ingenuity and the grandeur of ancient civilizations. Located on the Giza Plateau, just outside Cairo, Egypt, this awe-inspiring monument is the oldest and largest of the three pyramids in the Giza pyramid complex.\n\nBuilt around 2560 BC during the reign of Pharaoh Khufu, the Great Pyramid served as the final resting place for the pharaoh, symbolizing his divine connection and immortal journey to the afterlife. Constructed with astonishing precision and engineering skill, it is an architectural marvel that continues to baffle modern experts. The pyramid\'s colossal limestone blocks were quarried and transported, and its alignment with the cardinal points is an extraordinary display of ancient astronomical knowledge.\n\nRising 481 feet (147 meters) into the sky, the Great Pyramid was once encased in smooth, polished white limestone, reflecting the rays of the sun and gleaming like a radiant jewel on the horizon. Today, although the outer casing has eroded over millennia, the pyramid remains a majestic and enigmatic structure that beckons visitors from around the globe to witness its enduring mystery and connect with the ancient civilization that once thrived along the banks of the Nile. As you step into the shadows of this extraordinary monument, prepare to be awestruck by the Great Pyramid\'s monumental legacy and the fascinating stories it holds within its timeless walls.', 'Explore the wonders of the ancient world with the Great Pyramid of Giza! Discover the mysteries behind this awe-inspiring pyramid, marvel at its precision engineering, and delve into its rich history as the tomb of Pharaoh Khufu. Uncover the secrets of its construction and alignment, and learn about its status as the last standing wonder of the ancient world. Unravel the enigma surrounding this magnificent structure, and embark on a virtual journey to one of humanity\'s greatest architectural achievements.', '/IMG/Great_pyramid_of_Giza/mini_background.jpg', '/IMG/Great_pyramid_of_Giza/cover.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/u1S9p3IfCV0', 'Al Haram, Giza Governorate, Egypt.', 'To get to the Great Pyramid of Giza, follow these steps:\n\n1. Fly to Cairo: The journey to the Great Pyramid of Giza usually starts with a flight to Cairo International Airport in Egypt. Cairo is well-connected to major cities worldwide, and the airport serves as the main gateway to the country.\n\n2. Travel to Giza: From Cairo, you can travel to the Giza Pyramid Complex by road, which takes approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on traffic conditions. There are several transportation options available:\n\n- Taxi or Ride-Sharing: Taking a taxi or using ride-sharing services is a common and direct way to reach the Giza Pyramid Complex. Taxi stands are available in various locations in Cairo.\n\n- Tour Buses: Many organized tours offer trips to the Giza Pyramid Complex. You can join a tour group for a guided visit to the pyramids.\n\n3. Arriving at the Great Pyramid of Giza: Once you arrive at the Giza Pyramid Complex, you will find designated entrances for visitors. The Great Pyramid is the largest and most prominent pyramid, making it easily identifiable.', 'Metro: Cairo has a metro system that connects different parts of the city. You can take Line 2, which goes to Giza, and then use a taxi or other means of transportation to reach the pyramids.', 'If you\'re traveling to the Great Pyramid of Giza by private vehicle, there are parking facilities available near the complex. However, visitors are not allowed to park their vehicles inside the pyramid area.', 'The Giza Pyramid Complex is designed to be accessible to visitors. However, it\'s essential to note that the pyramids themselves involve climbing steep and narrow passages, which may not be suitable for individuals with mobility challenges.', 'The travel time from Cairo city center to the Giza Pyramid Complex is approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on the mode of transportation and traffic conditions.', '- Be prepared for intense heat, especially during the summer months. Wear appropriate clothing, hats, and sunscreen to protect yourself from the sun.\n- Avoid touching or climbing on the ancient structures to preserve their integrity for future generations.\n- Engage the services of a licensed tour guide if you want to learn about the history and significance of the pyramids.', 'For more information or inquiries, you can contact the local guide tour at: <a href=\'https://www.pyramid-of-giza.com\' target=\"_blank\">www.pyramid-of-giza.com</a>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3456.041638829343!2d31.13076976103458!3d29.97823332485261!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x14584587ac8f291b%3A0x810c2f3fa2a52424!2sThe%20Great%20Pyramid%20of%20Giza!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1690463956471!5m2!1sen!2s', 11);

